05/07/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Chief Prosecutor Boris Velchev announced on Wednesday (5 July) that he has asked the High Judicial Council to dismiss two top prosecutors, Tseko Yordanov and Angel Iliev. 
A recent inspection of their work reportedly uncovered a large number of irregularities and violations. 
The two have refused to resign.
On Tuesday, Interior Minister Rumen Petkov announced that 24 indictments for corruption were submitted against senior state officials and magistrates between January and June. 
He refused to provide specific names. 
(Dnevnik, Sega, Monitor - 05/07/06; Mediapool - 04/07/06)
